   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/acadian/Romero_Laura_Mae_T739_T970.abs.pdf">Interview includes discussion of Romero's family, sewing for two companies in New
            Orleans, sewing for the Acadian Handicraft Project, sewing for other individuals once
            the Acadian Handicraft Project ended, techniques for making christening dresses,
            designing patterns for clothes, making a heirloom dress for her granddaughter, a dress
            she made was in Sew Beautiful Magazine, making christening dresses for her daughters,
            grandchildren, and great grandchildren, colors used for clothes made for Acadian
            Handicraft Project, and the materials Romero prefers.</abstract>
